AddressInfo.Title: E-bike charging station George-Bähr-Str. 14
AddressInfo.AccessComments: Sockets are located on the green strip to the right at one of the central light blue basement windows (the one under the signs ‘Einfahrt freihalten!’ und ‘Feuerwehrzufahrt’) in the driveway of the yellow multi-family house with the address: George-Bähr-Straße 14, 01069 Dresden. The white socket distributor either hangs out or lies protected on top of the tilted window. Don't forget to switch it on with the small switch on the side (white LED in front must light up)!

Connections.Comments: Bicycles/e-bikes only. 2x Schuko (Type F, CEE 7/3; 230V/16A), 2x USB-A (5V/2.4A) and 1x USB-C (5V/3A) (USB-A + USB-C max. 3.4A). On request I can provide Shimano Steps chargers (EC-E6000 42V/4.0A, EC-E6002 42V/1.8A) and USB cables as well as bike tools, an air pump and maybe a spare part or two.

GeneralComments: Bicycles/e-bikes only. If you have any questions, please call us at +49 1512 2862747 or send us a message via SMS/Threema/Telegram/Signal/Keybase (24/7). We are also very happy about a short note that you are charging or planning to charge! :) If a neighbour asks, refer to family ‘Jahn/Strätz’. Free WiFi available without registration (‘Freifunk’).  Free WCs available in numerous public university buildings on the other side of the street (e.g. Zeuner-Bau, 30 m). Restaurants/cafés nearby: Dersim (200 m), Bäckerei Möbius (250 m), Grill Cube (350 m), Nürnberger Platz (350 m). Bicycles can be locked directly to the window grille. Have a good ride!
